{"title":"Ari Delano Peak Adds More Travel, New Suspension, Same Frame","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2024-ari-delano-peak-trail-bike/","date":1718294400000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/ari-delano-peak-2025-feature-1536x861.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"861\" alt=\"2024 ari delano peak trail mountain bike with longer travel rear in a factory\" /></p>\n<p>The Ari Delano Peak trail bike is getting a little boost thanks to its metric shock standard and the new Rockshox suspension that just launched.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By mounting a slightly longer-stroke rear, the Delano Peak goes to 142mm rear travel, up from 135mm. It keeps the 150mm forks, so there are no changes to geometry, just a 5% gain in rear travel. Meaning, you can replace the 210×50 rear shock on your existing Delano Peak with a 210×55 and get the extra travel, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Three new complete bike builds are offered with the longer travel, plus a frameset:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Comp.jpg\"><img width=\"2100\" height=\"1157\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Comp.jpg\" alt=\"2024 ari delano peak comp\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Comp.jpg 2100w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Comp-297x164.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Comp-1536x846.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Comp-120x66.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Comp-768x423.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Comp-2048x1128.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Delano Peak Comp ($3,899)</strong><br />DVO Diamond 36 D1 SL/ Topaz Gen 3, Shimano SLX Drivetrain, TRP Slate EVO Brakes, and E-thirteen Sylvan Core wheels.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Elite.jpg\"><img width=\"2310\" height=\"1321\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Elite.jpg\" alt=\"2024 ari delano peak elite\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Elite.jpg 2310w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Elite-297x170.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Elite-1536x878.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Elite-120x69.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Elite-768x439.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Elite-2048x1171.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Delano Peak Elite ($4,899)</strong><br />Rockshox Charger 3.1 Lyrik Ultimate/Super Deluxe Ultimate, Shimano XT Drivetrain, Shimano XT 4-piston brakes, and DT Swiss M 1900 Spline wheels.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Pro.jpg\"><img width=\"2100\" height=\"1178\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Pro.jpg\" alt=\"2024 ari delano peak pro\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Pro.jpg 2100w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Pro-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Pro-1536x862.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Pro-120x67.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Pro-768x431.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-Pro-2048x1149.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Delano Peak Pro ($5,899)</strong><br />Rockshox Charger 3.1 Lyrik Ultimate/Super Deluxe Ultimate, SRAM GX Transmission, SRAM Maven Silver, and DT Swiss XM 1700 Spline wheels.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-frameset.jpg\"><img width=\"2310\" height=\"1321\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-frameset.jpg\" alt=\"2024 ari delano peak frameset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-frameset.jpg 2310w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-frameset-297x170.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-frameset-1536x878.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-frameset-120x69.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-frameset-768x439.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/2024-Ari-Delano-frameset-2048x1171.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Delano Peak Frameset ($2,299)</strong><br />Includes Rockshox Charger 3.1 Super Deluxe Ultimate shock.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All prices are MSRP, but all complete bikes are $300-$400 off MSRP at time of posting.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://aribikes.com/products/delano-peak\">AriBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2024-ari-delano-peak-trail-bike/\">Ari Delano Peak Adds More Travel, New Suspension, Same Frame</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"cd66169d3e319ae742717d192b98711571ed417c8e55c3ebb5946a23e30ebd9d","category":"Cycling"}